translated: Ernberg, Carl Ivar Lars, city legal adviser, Gothenburg, born on July 15, 1901 in Stockholm to Captain Ivar E. and Anna Gustafva Mathilda Remahl. Married in 1942 to Maja Petersen. Completed high school exams in Gothenburg in 1920, obtained law degree in Uppsala in 1933. Served as judge in Askim's, Hisingen's and Sävedal's district courts from 1933-1936, and has been a city legal adviser in Gothenburg since 1937.
